S-transform is a timeâfrequency representation of non-stationary signals that combines the positives of short-time Fourier transform and WT for a satisfactory timeâfrequency distribution. The S-transform can be considered as a phase-corrected WT, thereby offering more precise data on the local features of a signal in the timeâfrequency domain [118â120]. In [121], a protection scheme is suggested for radial/meshed MGs using differential protection and S-transform concepts. The differential currents of protected line terminals and differential fault energy (Ediff\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
